title: T-11-03 — Implement immutable repair path
updated_at: "2026-07-19T06:23:17Z"
---
Bundle provenance: WP-11 / T-11-03

Allow human-corrected representations with provenance and supersession without changing originals.

Deliverables:
- Repair workflow
- Repair review UI contract

Acceptance criteria:
- Repair creates a new representation version
- Original and faulty representation remain inspectable
- Dependent source units are regenerated and invalidated correctly
- Units whose canonical records are unchanged retain identity across repair versions; InvalidationRequest contains the sorted unique union of removed IDs and same-ID units whose canonical record changed (including locator/provenance shifts)
- At most one representation version per source file enters any unitization, exact-map, lexical-index, or other derived projection input
- SourceRepresentation schema/interface gains optional supersedesId before repaired records are audited or unitized; legacy schema-version-1 records remain readable
- Approval is human-only through an injected authorization policy over ActorHandle; agents and deterministic auditors may advise or validate but cannot approve
- Approval requires a nonblank rationale, and a reviewer cannot edit a proposal; rejection and correction append new linked records while preserving prior proposals and artifacts
- Proposal and approval mutations use expected revisions and idempotency keys, commit atomically, and recover post-commit invalidation delivery without duplicate logical requests
- Invalidation recovery has delivery-only authority and returns the exact replayed request IDs; it cannot transition repair state
- Fresh-process recovery reads and acknowledges the durable invalidation outbox through an explicit repository-backed port; append-only ledger writes alone are not treated as a recovery reader
- Repaired unitization keeps the canonical SourceFile immutable and qualifies corrected locator bounds with a non-persisted view bound to the immutable CorrectionArtifact size/hash

Test surfaces:
- workflow
- recovery
- migration